<subSubSection pageId="127" pageNumber="886" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="127.[2059,2652,2849,3276]" lastBlockId="127.[1448,2653,3284,3474]" pageId="127" pageNumber="886">
Cytochrome-b divergence of 0-6% occurs between S. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Goodman, Jenkins &amp; Ratrimomanarivo" authorityYear="2005" box="[2226,2364,3170,3199]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tandrefana">tandrefana</taxonomicName>
and S. 
<taxonomicName box="[2477,2599,3170,3199]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="127" pageNumber="886" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marovaza">marovaza</taxonomicName>
, indicative of within-species divergence, but it does not provide support for recognition oftandrefana as a valid species; additional research is needed. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
